window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>For the first time, all of the short fiction set in James S. A. Corey’s </b><b><i>New York Times</i></b><b> bestselling Expanse series are available in this collection - Now a major television series.</b>&nbsp;</p> <p><b>From </b><b><i>Leviathan Wakes</i></b><b> to </b><b><i>Leviathan Falls</i></b><b>, James S. A. Corey’s Hugo Award-winning Expanse series has redefined modern space opera.</b>&nbsp;</p> <p>On Mars, a scientist experiments with a new engine that will one day become to drive that fuels humanity’s journey into the stars.&nbsp;</p> <p>On an asteroid station, a group of prisoners are oblivious to the catastrophe that awaits them.&nbsp;</p> <p>On a future Earth beset by overpopulation, pollution, and poverty, a crime boss desperately seeks to find a way off planet.&nbsp;</p> <p>On an alien world, a human family struggles to establish a colony and make a new home.&nbsp;</p> <p>All these stories and more are featured in this unmissable collection of short fiction set in the hard scrabble world of The Expanse.&nbsp;</p> <p>Contents:&nbsp;</p> <ul> <li>The Expanse Short Fiction&nbsp;</li> <li>Drive&nbsp;</li> <li>The Butcher of Anderson Station&nbsp;</li> <li>The Churn&nbsp;</li> <li>Gods of Risk&nbsp;</li> <li>The Vital Abyss&nbsp;</li> <li>Strange Dogs&nbsp;</li> <li>Auberon&nbsp;</li> <li>The Sins of our Fathers&nbsp;&nbsp;</li> </ul>"; 
